<para id="fs-idm207483440">It is important to remember that even though Tony’s costs stepped up when he exceeded his original capacity (relevant range), the <emphasis effect="italics">behavior</emphasis> of the costs did not change. His fixed costs still remained fixed in total and his total variable cost rose as the number of T-shirts he produced rose. <link target-id="fs-idm202141104"/> summarizes how costs behave within their relevant ranges.</para>
